ZnSO4 and Zn-NCDs treatments increased growth indexes compared to the control. However, no significant difference in root length and dry weight increase was observed between ZnSO4 and Zn-NCDs1 treatments (Fig. 5
                           a and Table 3
                           ). In shoot, Zn-NCDs1 treatment significantly increased shoot length and shoot dry weight compared to ZnSO4 treatment (Table 3). The findings indicated that increasing the Zn-NCDs concentration increased the growth indexes. Therefore, Zn-NCDs3 had the highest levels of these indicators.
